data.value: The averaging coefficient is how many times the oven temp is averaged before being displayed. A higher number means the temperature is more accurate however it will take longer to update. A low number means the temperature may be less accurate but it will update quickly. The default value is 10.

data.name: Label59.Text
data.value:
The oven temperture sensor uses a type-K thermo couple. The operating range is from 100°F - 750°F. Fo saftey reasons the oven should not be run past 700°F for prolonged periods. The oven is hard coded shut down past 750°F
The case temperature sensor uses a linear active thermistor. The oven is hard coded to shut down at 150°F.

data.name: Label13.Text
data.value:
This is the characteristic reflow curve however the time and temperatures will change depending on many factors. Board size, density, component types, all play a factor in how well your board will reflow. Obtaining an accurate profile will require testing and experimentation. Once the profile is obtained it can be saved and reused at anytime.
There are two methods of creating profiles using this software: 1) Profile Editor 2) Profile Designer
The Profile Editor allows you to edit pre-defined points in the characteristic curve. This method is fastest and easiest to setup however it is limited to the standard curve and cannot be customized.
The Profile Designer is a script based editor environment. It allows manipulation of all controls and can be used to create custom curves. The Profile Designer was designed to be a simple yet powerful tool however it will take longer to master.
For most applications the Profile Editor will be sufficient. Each allows the Profile to be saved and recalled later.
The time and temperature cannot both be set as one is a function of the other. For instance, an aluminum core board will take longer to reach 200°C then a FR4 board. The Profile Editor allows a choice between both however.
Both allow the temperature to be logged at user defined time intervals using the Data Logger. The data is populated in two textboxes and can be copied for use in other applications ( spreadsheet, data base, etc).
